================
description
================

1) This program accept file name with position from user and read 20 bytes from that
position.
2) if open gets successful then it will show(read) requested number of bytes from that file.
3) Required filename will be taken from command line

================
about the code
================

	input	:	file name, position
	output	:	result - display 20 bytes of data from requested position
 			
=============
How to run
=============

	make	:	compile the code and generates executable file as "myexe"
	make run:	run the executable with command line argument
			for this you have to pass parameter as: 
			
			$ make run p1="parameter_value1" p2="parameter_value2"
	
=============
NOTE
=============

	1)If the given file is unable to open, it will display the appropriate reason.
